# Keep docs in sync with every change

Any change to the repository (code, build, structure, behavior) **must** be reflected in:

| File / dir | Update when |
| --- | --- |
| `CHANGELOG.md` | Always — add an entry under the current unreleased/version section (Added / Changed / Removed / Fixed / Known issues). Source of truth. |
| `README.md` | Layout, build steps, usage, requirements, or links changed. |
| `docs/` | Behavior/feature/version changes mirrored into the relevant page (see below). |
| `docs/index.html` | Version, downloads, quick-start, doc links, or top-level messaging changed (GitHub Pages landing). |

## docs/ targets

- `docs/index.html` — **GitHub Pages landing page** (https://tuyndoan.github.io/nssm/). Update whenever the current version, download links, quick-start commands, doc links, or top-level messaging change. Published via `.github/workflows/pages.yml` (deploys `docs/` on push to `main`). Keep its self-contained styling/dark-mode in sync with the roadmap/release pages.
- `docs/roadmap/roadmap-data.js` — backlog/version/task changes (also see `roadmap-backlog-sync.mdc`).
- `docs/release/<x.y.z>/release-data.js` — interactive release-notes content (HTML viewer) for the version.
- `docs/release/<x.y.z>/RELEASE.md` — **GitHub Release body**. CI (`.github/workflows/build.yml`) publishes this verbatim via `gh release create --notes-file` on a `v<x.y.z>` tag. Keep it in sync with the `CHANGELOG.md` section for that version.
- `docs/manual.txt` — usage/CLI/registry behavior changes.

> **Pages note:** links inside `docs/*.html` must work when served from Pages (root = `docs/`). Reference files **outside** `docs/` (e.g. `CHANGELOG.md`) via their GitHub URL — `https://github.com/tuyndoan/nssm/blob/main/<path>` — not a relative `../../` path. New pages need a **Home** link back to `docs/index.html`. If a binary/asset must be skipped by Pages, remember `docs/.nojekyll` disables Jekyll processing.

## Release notes (per version)

When cutting a new version `<x.y.z>`, before tagging `v<x.y.z>`:

1. Create `docs/release/<x.y.z>/RELEASE.md` (Markdown; this is what users see on the GitHub Releases page). Mirror the highlights/fixed/known-issues from the matching `CHANGELOG.md` section.
2. Update `docs/release/<x.y.z>/release-data.js` for the interactive HTML viewer.
3. If `RELEASE.md` is missing, CI falls back to an auto-generated note — so always add it for a real release.

## Rules

1. **No silent changes.** If you touch behavior, build, or structure, update `CHANGELOG.md` in the same change set.
2. **Versioning continues from upstream 2.24** — next is `2.25`, then `2.26`, … (no fork bump to 3.x).
3. **English only** across `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, and `docs/`.
4. **Maintainer:** Tuyn Doan.
5. Before finishing, verify links and version numbers are consistent across all three.

## Quick checklist

- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md` entry added/updated.
- [ ] `README.md` updated if build/layout/usage/links changed.
- [ ] Matching `docs/` page (roadmap / release / manual) updated.
- [ ] `docs/index.html` landing page updated if version, downloads, quick start, links, or messaging changed.
- [ ] For a release: `docs/release/<x.y.z>/RELEASE.md` exists and matches the CHANGELOG section.
- [ ] Pages links valid (off-repo files use GitHub URLs; new pages link Home).
- [ ] Versions and links consistent everywhere; English only.
